  "paper_analysis": {
    "summary": "This paper studies graphene/monolayer xenon (G/mXe) heterostructures, where annealing and Xe pressure tune the Xe lattice constant and thereby continuously tune a high-order moiré period from nanometers to effectively infinity. Lab-based ARPES directly observes graphene Dirac-cone replicas moving in momentum space and, in the commensurate limit, a Kekulé-distortion gap at the Dirac point from intervalley coupling; a continuum moiré Hamiltonian is used to explain the spectra and predict narrow moiré bands.",
    "measurement_types": [
      "angle-resolved photoemission spectroscopy (ARPES)",
      "low-energy electron diffraction (LEED)",
      "scanning tunneling microscopy (STM)",
      "sample annealing / temperature-dependent in-situ tuning",
      "pressure-controlled Xe deposition"
    ],
